Why are laws enforced in Singapore?
I'm talking to local businessman Chang, sitting in an outdoor diner.
Commenting on the situation in Singapore, Chang smokes one cigarette after another, while he carefully stores the cigarettes in a metal box he brought from his office.
After the conversation, the businessman goes to the nearest urn, a hundred yards away, and throws the bulls in.
