Recent tests of asylum seekers in Sweden who were subjected to a new medical age assessment method show that more than 80 percent of those tested were rated as over 18, but not everyone trusts the accuracy of these results.
The Swedish National Agency for Forensic Medicine (Rättsmedicinalverket) started testing earlier this year.
