A Spanish official was fired after not going to work for 10 years.
What angel-like patience (or total indifference to public office) was the boss of Spanish official Carlos Río to have?
The permanent absence stretched on for 10 long years.
However, Mr. Recio was fired.
But not by his immediate superior.
Which is not the case in a bureaucratic world.
The common people seem to have long been used to all the crap of the "servant of the people".
