Crimea shares the plant of champagne "New World"
The State Unitary Enterprise of the Republic of Crimea "New World Champagne Wine Plant" has been decided to be acquired by transforming it into the OJSC "New World Champagne Wine Plant", according to the order of the Minister of Property and Land Relations of Crimea Anna Anyuhina.
100% of the company's shares will remain in the state ownership of Crimea.
The share capital of the joint stock company will be 595.5 million rubles and will consist of 5,955 million ordinary shares with a nominal value of 100 rubles each .
The Ministry of Agriculture of Crimea stated that if within the next three years funds were not found to modernize the enterprise, the plant would be threatened with closure.
The wear and tear of the main assets at the enterprise is about 60-70%.
