What's left is not enough to implement the modernization plan.
"It is problematic to get money from the owner, it is difficult to talk about attracting loan funds from large credit organizations", - said the Deputy Head of the Ministry of Agriculture of Crimea Sergey Petelin in April this year.
The Parliament of Crimea included the enterprise in the forecast plan for privatization in 2017 .
It was proposed to stockpile it and put it up for auction.
The "Interfax" source in the Crimean authorities estimated the possible cost of selling the enterprise at $40 million, the investor's investment in modernization - another $30 million.
"New World" in 2016 increased the production of sparkling wines by 2.8% compared to 2015 level - to 1,52 million bottles.
