The murder of a journalist highlights that Mexico is becoming increasingly dangerous.
The staff of the weekly newspaper Riodosse usually meets on Wednesdays to discuss plans to cover the latest violent crimes in Sinaloa state, including organized crime, corrupt officials or the ongoing drug war.
But today, overwhelmed by their own tragedy, they met to talk about security.
They were told that they needed to change their habits.
