Despite the risks and the fact that the launch was postponed (instead of December 2015, the Soyuz took off on April 28, 2016), the idea proved to be correct, a source at the spaceport told Kommersant: "Otherwise we would not have launched a single launch from the Vostochny spacecraft, but would have been engaged in construction".
Vice-premier Dmitry Rogozin, who was in charge of the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrei Ochlopkov his "cosmic Susanin", but it was almost always him who requested information about the construction process.
Mr. Ochlopkov is also remembered for his frankness: for example, in an interview with "Ъ" he proposed to strip the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Specstroy) of the status of the sole contractor for the Eastern part of the city and work directly with subcontractors: "Why should we put all the eggs in one basket of the Special Construction?"
This idea found support in the government.
Since 2017, CENKI has assumed the duties of general contractor to complete the construction and installation work on the start-up and technical complex by the fourth quarter.
According to the "Kommersant", Mr. Ochlopkov's move to a new job was due to disagreements with the CENKI leadership regarding the way to complete the construction of the facilities and complexes of the cosmodrome, as well as the methods of working with subcontractors.
"It was decided that this would be best for everyone", says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the East Building.
A government official, in turn, called the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, it will be difficult to find an equivalent replacement".
According to the "Kommersant", this will not be necessary: the post of technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be distributed among the divisions of the CENKI.
