His lawyer, Andrei Orlov, did not rule out appealing the verdict in the cassation court of the Moscow city court and the Supreme Court.
"We will use all the leverage up to the European Court of Human Rights", he told RIA Novosti.
Anton Mamaev, a 28-year-old resident of Moscow, suffering from spinal muscular atrophy, became a defendant in the criminal case last fall.
