On June 30, the Timiryazevsky district court of Moscow sentenced Vasily Seroshtanov to three years in prison, and Anton Mamaev to four and a half years in prison with imprisonment in a general regime colony (according to part 2 of Article 162 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After the disabled man was placed in the SIZO, the Public Chamber, the Prosecutor General's Office, the Commissioner for Human Rights under President Tatyana Moskalkov joined the case.
