Russia will see the emergence of two new territories of rapid social and economic development - "Ababa" and "Novotroytsk".
The relevant decree of the Russian Government will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activities of the TOR in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are defined.
The city, which has a population of 15,000, will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investment by residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments to the city, as well as create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities in which the special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will be applied in the TOR "Abaza" includes, for example, plant breeding, animal husbandry, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the territory's dependence on the city-forming enterprise of the "Abakansky mine" LLC.
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakassia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroytsk, a territory of advanced social and economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the monopoly city, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of Ural Steel, as well as create more than 2,3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities that will enjoy special legal protection for entrepreneurs in the new TOR includes, in particular, freshwater fisheries, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroytsk became the first of the monogroup of the Orenburg region to receive the status of a TOR.
Recall that the territory of rapid development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR, the following can be distinguished: income tax of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential regime of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates for rental.
