In Moscow, a policeman shot a man in the leg defending himself from an attack
A policeman shot a fighter in Moscow in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On August 3, the evening of the police department of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs in the Yakimanka district received a report about a fight on the street of Customs, 46.
"The police arrived to intercept the crime and disbanded the participants in the conflict", - reported RIA Novosti, citing the press service of the head of the interior ministry.
According to police, when one of the participants in the conflict attacked an employee of the Ministry of Internal Affairs with a piece of glass, the policeman warned the man several times about the use of weapons and fired a warning shot.
That didn't stop the bully, and then a law enforcement officer shot the man in the leg.
The injured man needed to be hospitalized.
